Annotation3.Text:
This model illustrates Simulink variant subsystems. Variant subsystems let you 
provide multiple implementations for a subsystem where only one 
implementation is active during simulation. You can programmatically swap out 
the active implementation and replace it with one of the other implementations 
without modifying the model.
